						<summary>

						<p>Slab near the forest boundary 3 miles to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the demarcation of the boundaries between Māḍupūru and Nārāyaṇarājupeṭa was set up by certain individual by name Gōgulapalle Gura[m]payya. In characters of 17th century A.D.</p>						

